define({"topics":[{"title":"What is a server community?","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">A server community is a group of people belonging to the same directory or user registry, such as your corporate directory, or external server communities outside of your organization. Your administrator determines which server communities are available to you.<\/p>","href":"c_st8_uim_servercom_whatis.html","attributes":{"data-id":"c_st8_uim_servercom_whatis"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"c_st8_uim_servercom_whatis-d433e369","topics":[]},{"title":"How do I connect to more than one server community?","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You connect to a server community by adding it to your client and logging in to it. When you add a server community, an icon such as <img class=\"image\" src=\"images\/ST9_community_2_awareness_05.JPG\" alt=\"Active community icon\"\/> shows for that server community in the expandable area in your status card. This icon indicates whether you are logged in to the server community and your availability status. For example, \"I am Available,\" is the status as shown in the preceding server community icon.<\/p>","href":"t_st8_uim_servercom.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_st8_uim_servercom"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_st8_uim_servercom-d433e380","topics":[]},{"title":"How do I chat with people who are members of a public instant messaging network?","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">If your system administrator connects one of your server communities to any public instant messaging networks, you can chat with members of those networks. <\/p>","href":"t_st8_uim_otherIM.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_st8_uim_otherIM"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_st8_uim_otherIM-d433e393","topics":[]}]});